<dt class="postheader">
主题: <strong>【Wilderness Origins】唤魂师变体：御守唤魂师（Ward Spiritualist）</strong><br>
作者: <strong>lk9551</strong> 于 <strong>2021-07-25, 周日 10:07:42</strong>
<dd class="postbody">
<span style="font-size: 14pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>御守唤魂师（Ward Spiritualist）【唤魂师变体】</strong></span><br><br>出自：《荒野缘起》（Wilderness Origins pg. 18）<br><br>虽然许多唤魂师都被一个逝去的灵魂所束缚，这种情况更可能是偶然或悲剧的结果，而不是职业选择，但也有一些人寻求这种生活。一个御守唤魂师冒险进入荒野，并请求一个社神帮助她远行，她可以接受现有的御守，或者成为社神的新御守。<br><br><br><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">社神魅影（Kami Phantom，Su）：</span><br></strong>御守唤魂师的魅影没有大多数人强大，但它与她有着先天的联系。御守唤魂师的魅影是一个社神魅影，社神魅影的能力都与魅影相同，除了它的基础攻击加值等于它的生命骰的四分之三（如同盗贼）和它的生命骰是D8而不是D10。另外，社神魅影不能虚灵态显形，只能灵质态显形。<br><br>本能力调整了魅影。<br><br><br><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">守护灵器（Ward Implement，Su）：</span></strong><br>御守唤魂师获得了一个她选择的灵器学派，以及它的共鸣之力和基础灵器之力，如同秘学士。御守唤魂师不会从守护灵器中获得额外的已知法术，并且御守唤魂师的每日心智点总是等于其职业等级的一半（至少为1）。<br><br>当她获得她的守护灵器，御守唤魂师必须选择拥有一个灵器物品或自己成为器具。如果她选择拥有一个灵器物品，她的唤魂师法术会将它作为一个器材成分，当她在每天开始恢复法术时，她可以改变她的灵器物品是什么。她的灵器物品必须是可以单手拿的物品，不能是人造武器。如果御守唤魂师选择她自己成为灵器物品，她的唤魂师法术除了其他成分外，总是有一个姿势成分；这个成分不会变成情绪成分。<br><br>她可以移除法术的器材或姿势成分，但这需要进行专注检定（DC=15+两倍法术等级），思维成分的专注检定正常增加。<br><br>她在2级、6级、12级获得灵器学派的灵器之力，她必须满足这些灵器之力的先决条件，将她的唤魂师等级视为灵器之力先决条件的秘学士等级。她也可以将自己的唤魂师等级视为专长先决条件的秘学士等级。<br><br>本能力改变了施法，取代了连觉、魅影呼唤和高等魅影加护。<br><br><br><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size">融合显形（Merged Manifestation，Su）：</span></strong><br>在3级时，御守唤魂师学习如何将她的社神魅影与守护灵器融为一体。这是一种附身显形的效果，除了她不选择灵质态或虚灵态。作为替代，她获得不同的能力，效果取决于她是有一个灵器物品或自己成为器具。<br><br>如果她有一个灵器物品，当她使用融合显形时，她的工具视为一个符合体型的单手临时武器，并且她使用临时武器时不受到减值。此外，它被认为在融合显形的显现期间有+1增强加值。这个增强加值在8级时增加1，在13级和18级再次增加。在8级，和18级时，它所造成的伤害视同比实际大小增大1级。在13级，她的灵器物品在融合显形的显现期间也获得了感心之刃的效果。<br><br>如果她是自己的器具，当她使用融合显形时，她获得了1级Unchained武僧的徒手打击能力。在第8级，她的徒手攻击伤害相当于4级Unchained武僧，并获得1级Unchained武僧的疾风连击职业能力。在第13级，她的徒手攻击伤害相当于8级Unchained武僧，并且她的徒手攻击在融合显形的显现期间获得感心之刃的效果。18级时，她的徒手攻击伤害相当于12级Unchained武僧，并获得11级Unchained武僧的疾风连击职业能力。<br><br><div>Ward Spiritualist<br>Source Wilderness Origins pg. 18<br>While many spiritualists are bound to a departed spirit, a condition more likely to be the result of chance or tragedy than a career choice, there are some individuals who seek out this life. A ward spiritualist ventures into the wilderness and petitions a kami to help her in her travels, either taking an existing ward with her or becoming the kami’s new ward.<br><br>Kami Phantom (Su): The ward spiritualist’s phantom is less powerful than most, but it has an innate connection to its ward. The ward spiritualist’s phantom is a kami phantom, functioning as normal for a phantom, except that its base attack bonus is equal to three-quarters its Hit Dice (as a rogue) and its Hit Dice are d8s instead of d10s. Additionally, a kami phantom cannot manifest as incorporeal, only ectoplasmic.<br><br>This alters phantom.<br><br>Ward Implement (Su): The ward spiritualist gains a single implement school of her choice, as an occultist, along with its resonant focus power and base focus power. The ward spiritualist does not gain additional spells from her ward implement, and it always starts each day with mental focus invested equal to half her class level (minimum 1).<br><br>When she gains her ward implement, the ward spiritualist must choose either to have a physical implement or to be the implement herself. If she chooses to have a physical implement, her spiritualist spells include it as a focus component, and she can change what item is her implement when she regains her spells at the start of each day. Her implement must be an item that can be held in one hand, and it cannot be a manufactured weapon. If the ward spiritualist chooses to be her own ward implement, her spiritualist spells always have a somatic component in addition to their other components; this component does not become an emotion component.<br><br>She can remove the focus or somatic component of her spells, but this requires a concentration check with a DC equal to 15 + twice the spell level, which is increased for a thought component as normal.<br><br>She gains a focus power for her implement school at 2nd level, and again at 6th level and 12th level. She must meet the prerequisites of these focus powers, treating her spiritualist level as her occultist level for focus power prerequisites. She also treats her spiritualist level as her occultist level for feat prerequisites.<br><br>This alters spellcasting and replaces bonded senses, phantom recall, and greater spiritual interference.<br><br>Merged Manifestation (Su): At 3rd level, the ward spiritualist learns how to merge her kami phantom with her ward implement. This functions as bonded manifestation, except that she does not choose ectoplasmic or incorporeal. Instead, she gains different benefits depending on whether she has a physical implement or is her own implement.<br><br>If she has a physical implement, when using her merged manifestation, her implement functions as a one-handed improvised weapon of appropriate size, and she does not take the usual penalties associated with wielding an improvised weapon. Additionally, it is considered to have a +1 enhancement bonus for the duration of the merged manifestation. This enhancement bonus increases by 1 at 8th level, and again at 13th level and 18th level. At 8th level, and again at 18th level, it deals damage as a weapon one size category larger. At 13th level, her implement also gains the benefits of spirit-bound blade for the duration of the merged manifestation.<br><br>If she is her own implement, when using her merged manifestation, she gains the unarmed strike class feature as a 1st level unchained monk. At 8th level, her unarmed strike damage is that of a 4th-level unchained monk, and she gains flurry of blows as a 1st-level unchained monk. At 13th level, her unarmed damage is that of an 8th-level unchained monk, and her unarmed strikes gain the benefits of spirit-bound blade for the duration of the merged manifestation. At 18th level, her unarmed damage is that of a 12th level unchained monk, and she can use flurry of blows as an 11th-level unchained monk.</div>
